Going to newer versions of hibernate 5.1.17 and above + postgres seems to have exhibited this behavior. Looking into the code, when it binds a type that has no value, the old hibernate code attempted to resolve the type through a typeresolver. The newer versions of hibernate&#39;s implementation state that it will not guess.  

      public Type resolveParameterBindType(Object bindValue) {
    		if ( bindValue == null ) {
    			// we can&#39;t guess
    			return null;
    		}


We ended up just setting a default value based on the type first, and then the real null value.

